Job Details

As a Senior Consultant, you will work with colleagues and clients to develop QlikView and QlikSense applications interfacing with Oracle, Teradata, SAP databases, and Business Objects universes. Your role includes assessing data quality, designing network and system architectures, diagnosing system behavior, and creating administrative scripts.

Key Responsibilities:

Develop QlikView and Qlik Sense applications.

Interface with various databases and data sources.

Assess and remediate data quality issues.

Integrate 3rd party software such as Snap Logic, GeoQlik or NPrinting into Qlik Sense applications

Design and implement network/system architectures.

Analyze network communication and diagnose system behavior.

Develop and maintain administration best practices.

Install and administer Qlik Sense software and servers.

Integrate third-party software into Qlik Sense applications.

Design and develop mobile applications.

Assist with Qlik Sense Server integration issues.

Develop solutions for client problems.

Establish and maintain customer relationships.

Identify and document process/data quality issues.

Propose and implement solutions, including client training.

Define project schedules and publish progress reports.

Requirements/Qualifications:

Technical Skills:

Significant experience with Qlik Sense application development.

2-3 years of database development using star schema.

Experience with Windows Server, Qlik Sense Server/Publisher, and Virtual Machines.
